## PHASE 1: VISUAL FORENSICS (THE "JOKULA" DNA)

### 1. The Minimalist Grid Layout

**Principle:** Clean, spacious grid system that allows content to breathe. Focus on visual hierarchy through whitespace.

**Implementation:**
- **Project Gallery:** Grid-based layout with consistent spacing
  - **Desktop:** Multi-column grid (typically 2-3 columns)
  - **Tablet:** 2-column grid
  - **Mobile:** Single column stack
- **Content Sections:** Generous padding and margins
- **Image Display:** Full-width or contained with consistent aspect ratios

**Technical Specifications:**
```css
/* Project Gallery Grid */
.project-gallery {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 2rem;
  padding: 4rem 2rem;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .project-gallery {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 3rem;
    padding: 6rem 4rem;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .project-gallery {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 4rem;
    padding: 8rem 6rem;
  }
}
```

**Visual Rules:**
- Maintain consistent gaps between grid items
- Use generous padding around sections
- Allow images to maintain their aspect ratios
- Create visual breathing room between elements

